description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and highly motivated nurse to join our Urology Macmillan Nursing Team, within the Surgical Division of the acute Trust. As a busy regional unit we are committed to delivering a quality service to our cancer patients and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves supporting the Urology Macmillan Clinical Nurse Specialist to provide a quality service for the cancer patients and their families throughout their cancer journey. You will be instrumental in driving the Personalised Care agenda , including Holistic Needs Assessment and Health and Wellbeing clinics, promoting a culture that supports and enables self-management. You will play a key role in co-ordination of the patient pathway and nurse led clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A back ground in Urology/ Cancer /Oncology or palliative care would be an essential to the role. Excellent communication skills and an ability to prioritise workload, whilst working as part of a team is also necessary. It is essential to have basic IT skills and previous experience working with CERNER an advantage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Previous applicants need not apply*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There will be an opportunity to develop skills and access training via Macmillan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Matron Silverio 0151 6785111 Ex 8628 Bleep 4970&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
